[Tue 2026-04-21 05:15 PDT] Build a Customer Win-Back Engine for this ASP.NET MVC video rental app (Vidly). This is an autonomous service that identifies lapsed customers, classifies why they left, generates personalized re-engagement campaigns, and tracks win-back outcomes.

Create these 3 files:

## 1. Vidly/Models/WinBackModels.cs

```csharp
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace Vidly.Models
{
    /// Why a customer lapsed
    public enum LapseReason
    {
        Inactivity,        // Simply stopped renting
        PriceShock,        // Last rentals had high fees/late charges
        NarrowTaste,       // Only rented one genre that dried up
        BadExperience,     // Multiple late fees or disputes
        SeasonalDropoff,   // Historically seasonal renter
        Unknown
    }

    /// Campaign type matched to lapse reason
    public enum CampaignType
    {
        WelcomeBack,       // Generic "we miss you" 
        PriceIncentive,    // Discount/free rental for price-shocked
        GenreExpansion,    // Suggest new genres based on taste
        LoyaltyRecovery,   // Bonus loyalty points
        SeasonalReminder,  // "Your favorite season is back"
        PersonalPick       // Staff-curated picks based on history
    }

    public enum WinBackStatus
    {
        Identified,    // Lapsed customer found
        Campaigned,    // Campaign generated
        Recovered,     // Customer rented again
        Lost           // No response after campaign window
    }

    /// A single win-back case
    public class WinBackCase
    {
        public int CustomerId { get; set; }
        public string CustomerName { get; set; }
        public string Email { get; set; }
        public MembershipType MembershipType { get; set; }
        public LapseReason LapseReason { get; set; }
        public CampaignType RecommendedCampaign { get; set; }
        public WinBackStatus Status { get; set; }
        public DateTime IdentifiedDate { get; set; }
        public DateTime? LastRentalDate { get; set; }
        public int DaysSinceLastRental { get; set; }
        public int TotalLifetimeRentals { get; set; }
        public decimal TotalLifetimeSpend { get; set; }
        public decimal LateFeeRatio { get; set; }  // late fees / total spend
        public string TopGenre { get; set; }
        public double GenreDiversity { get; set; }  // 0-1, Shannon entropy normalized
        public List<string> CampaignMessages { get; set; } = new List<string>();
        public double WinBackProbability { get; set; }  // estimated chance of recovery
        public string PersonalizedOffer { get; set; }
    }

    /// Dashboard summary
    public class WinBackSummary
    {
        public DateTime AnalysisDate { get; set; }
        public int TotalLapsedCustomers { get; set; }
        public int HighProbabilityTargets { get; set; }
        public int CampaignsGenerated { get; set; }
        public int RecoveredCustomers { get; set; }
        public decimal EstimatedRecoverableRevenue { get; set; }
        public Dictionary<LapseReason, int> ReasonBreakdown { get; set; } = new Dictionary<LapseReason, int>();
        public Dictionary<CampaignType, int> CampaignBreakdown { get; set; } = new Dictionary<CampaignType, int>();
        public List<WinBackCase> Cases { get; set; } = new List<WinBackCase>();
        public List<string> ProactiveInsights { get; set; } = new List<string>();
    }
}
```

## 2. Vidly/Services/WinBackService.cs

Create a service class `WinBackService` that:

Constructor takes: `ICustomerRepository`, `IRentalRepository`, `IMovieRepository`, `IClock` (from Services/IClock.cs — it has `DateTime Now { get; }`)

Key methods:
- `WinBackSummary Analyze(int lapseDaysThreshold = 60, int topN = 30)` — main analysis
- `WinBackCase AnalyzeCustomer(int customerId, int lapseDaysThreshold = 60)` — single customer  
- `IReadOnlyList<WinBackCase> GetHighProbabilityTargets(int lapseDaysThreshold = 60, double minProbability = 0.5)` — filtered list

Implementation details:
- Get all customers, get all rentals, build rental lookup by customer
- A customer is "lapsed" if their most recent rental was > lapseDaysThreshold days ago (use _clock.Now)
- **Lapse reason classification** — examine rental history to determine why:
  - PriceShock: if late fees > 30% of total spend in last 5 rentals
  - NarrowTaste: if Shannon entropy of genre distribution < 0.3 (normalized 0-1)
  - BadExperience: if > 40% of rentals had late fees
  - SeasonalDropoff: if rentals cluster in specific months (coefficient of variation of monthly counts > 1.5)
  - Inactivity: default if none of the above
- **Campaign matching** — map each LapseReason to a CampaignType and generate personalized messages:
  - PriceShock → PriceIncentive, message about a free rental or discount
  - NarrowTaste → GenreExpansion, suggest 2-3 genres they haven't tried
  - BadExperience → LoyaltyRecovery, apologize and offer bonus points
  - SeasonalDropoff → SeasonalReminder, mention their peak rental months
  - Inactivity → WelcomeBack with PersonalPick based on top genre
- **Win-back probability** — calculate 0-1 score based on: recency (closer = higher), lifetime value (more = higher), membership tier (higher = higher), late fee ratio (lower = higher). Use a weighted formula.
- **Personalized offer** — generate a text string like "Free rental of any {topGenre} movie" or "50% off your next 3 rentals"
- **Proactive insights** — generate 3-5 insights like "12 lapsed customers were heavy Action renters — consider expanding Action catalog" or "Price-shocked customers have 2.3x the late fee rate of active customers"
- **Estimated recoverable revenue** — sum of (avg monthly spend * 6 months * winBackProbability) for all cases

Use the same patterns as other services in this codebase (ChurnPredictorService, CustomerSegmentationService). Use `_clock.Now` instead of `DateTime.Now`.

For genre diversity, calculate Shannon entropy: H = -sum(p * ln(p)) / ln(n) where p is proportion of each genre and n is number of distinct genres.

## 3. Vidly/Controllers/WinBackController.cs

Follow the exact pattern of ChurnPredictorController:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Linq;
using System.Web.Mvc;
using Vidly.Repositories;
using Vidly.Services;

namespace Vidly.Controllers
{
    public class WinBackController : Controller
    {
        private readonly WinBackService _service;

        public WinBackController()
            : this(new InMemoryMovieRepository(), new InMemoryRentalRepository(),
                   new InMemoryCustomerRepository())
        {
        }

        public WinBackController(
            IMovieRepository movieRepository,
            IRentalRepository rentalRepository,
            ICustomerRepository customerRepository)
        {
            _service = new WinBackService(customerRepository, rentalRepository, movieRepository);
        }

        // GET: WinBack
        public ActionResult Index()
        {
            var summary = _service.Analyze();
            return View(summary);
        }

        // GET: WinBack/Customer/5
        public ActionResult Customer(int id)
        {
            try
            {
                var winBackCase = _service.AnalyzeCustomer(id);
                return Json(new { success = true, data = winBackCase }, JsonRequestBehavior.AllowGet);
            }
            catch (ArgumentException ex)
            {
                return Json(new { success = false, error = ex.Message }, JsonRequestBehavior.AllowGet);
            }
        }

        // GET: WinBack/Targets?minProbability=0.5
        public ActionResult Targets(double minProbability = 0.5)
        {
            var targets = _service.GetHighProbabilityTargets(minProbability: minProbability);
            return Json(targets, JsonRequestBehavior.AllowGet);
        }
    }
}
```

